==English==
===Etymology===
Origin uncertain; perhaps an abbreviation of [[shillaber]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ʃɪl/

===Verb===
{{en-verb|shill|shills|shilled|shilling}}

#To promote as a fan or customer.  
#To put under cover; to sheal.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|shill|shills}}
# A person paid to [[endorse]] a product favourably, while pretending to be [[impartial]].
# An accomplice at a confidence trick during an auction or gambling game.

===References===
*'''1994''': The pitchman swept his cane in a slow acceleration over the heads of the crowd and then suddenly pointed the silver cap toward Billy and the '''shill'''. — Cormac McCarthy, ''The Crossing''